{"TopicId":213185,"ForumId":119,"TopicTitle":"[SPOILERS] Purple-Yellow-Red lights seen while flying","CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T14:48:48Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T14:48:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo before launch there were these light artifacts in the videos.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022KSP2-Anomaly-1.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002298.42\u0022 height=\u0022659\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/mBj61HJ/KSP2-Anomaly-1.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022KSP2-Anomaly-1-2.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002271.00\u0022 height=\u0022753\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/YbtM98V/KSP2-Anomaly-1-2.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022KSP2-Anomaly-2.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002277.25\u0022 height=\u0022498\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/Kzzs299/KSP2-Anomaly-2.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022KSP2-Anomaly-3.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022135.21\u0022 height=\u0022937\u0022 width=\u0022693\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/sQWyDMz/KSP2-Anomaly-3.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve gone flying in that direction and in other places and I can confirm that I have seen these lights also on the Runway Island and in the Desert. Also, sometimes when I fly over the place where the lights appeared / blinked, I sometimes hear a deep SWOOSH sound.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut, I have not yet found any anomalies that are linked to the lights. So I am not sure if they are a regular game video rendering bug or something more.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-02-26T14:50:04Z\u0022 title=\u002202/26/2023 02:50  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 26, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Vl3d\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tstein","CreatedById":223854,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T14:51:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224244184\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022213185\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221677422928\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo before launch there were these light artifacts in the videos.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EHide contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/mBj61HJ/KSP2-Anomaly-1.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022KSP2-Anomaly-1.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002298.42\u0022 height=\u0022659\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/mBj61HJ/KSP2-Anomaly-1.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/YbtM98V/KSP2-Anomaly-1-2.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022KSP2-Anomaly-1-2.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002271.00\u0022 height=\u0022753\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/YbtM98V/KSP2-Anomaly-1-2.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/Kzzs299/KSP2-Anomaly-2.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022KSP2-Anomaly-2.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002277.25\u0022 height=\u0022498\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/Kzzs299/KSP2-Anomaly-2.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/sQWyDMz/KSP2-Anomaly-3.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022KSP2-Anomaly-3.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022135.21\u0022 height=\u0022937\u0022 width=\u0022693\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/sQWyDMz/KSP2-Anomaly-3.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve gone flying in that direction and in other places and I can confirm that I have seen these lights also on the Runway Island and in the Desert. Also, sometimes when I fly over the place where the lights appeared / blinked, I sometimes hear a deep SWOOSH sound.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut, I have not yet found any anomalies that are linked to the lights. So I am not sure if they are a regular game video rendering bug or something more.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe sad part is, there are so many bugs that\u00A0\u00A0 it is almost more likely to be a bug than something worth a theory \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stoup","CreatedById":2804,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T15:35:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve seen it a few times in flight too, but I didn\u0027t see anything in that direction. I\u0027m leaning more towards it being some kind of rendering bug, until anything comes around that might point to otherwise \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Razor235","CreatedById":16436,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T18:03:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it possible they\u0027re rendering bugs related to the other planets cresting the horizon?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket Farmer","CreatedById":71519,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-27T04:48:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224244509\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022213185\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221677434635\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002216436\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Razor235\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, Razor235 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it possible they\u0027re rendering bugs related to the other planets cresting the horizon?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI suppose anything is possible but that direction is North and most planets are more less in the same orbital plane around Kerbol\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"selfish_meme","CreatedById":125899,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-27T05:38:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve had Val\u0027s being thrown out of my plane regularly as I was flying\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jen X-1","CreatedById":223751,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-02T07:52:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224244273\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022213185\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221677425704\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00222804\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Stoup\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/26/2023 at 8:35 AM, Stoup said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve seen it a few times in flight too, but I didn\u0027t see anything in that direction. I\u0027m leaning more towards it being some kind of rendering bug, until anything comes around that might point to otherwise \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u2019s very much a rendering bug, I believe known as \u2018fireflies.\u2019 It\u2019s just a single infinitely bright pixel of any color occasionally appearing onscreen. The post processing sees it and decides to apply a crazy amount of bloom, causing those bright flashes. There\u2019s a simple fix for this, and I\u2019m sure the developers will fix this, though it\u2019s likely not a priority. I\u2019ve encountered this bug in KSP1 actually, with the TUFX post-processing mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jason_25","CreatedById":55730,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-03T23:07:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am still willing to believe these could be actual UFOs.\u00A0 Something like the Brown Mountain Lights or Marpa lights or Naga Lights or probably several others.\u00A0 The lights are definitely multi colored and much larger than a single pixel.\u00A0 They zip by the first mountain in the north of the space center and the mountain that the island runway is on.\u00A0 They also move back and forth.\u00A0 But if there is something causing a crack in the terrain the very much more colorful skybox in this game could be leaking through.\u00A0 So it could go either way.\u00A0 I like to think someone is observing the progress at the space center as the Kerbals get closer and closer to being a spacefaring civilization.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-03T23:20:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224244184\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022213185\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221677422928\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/26/2023 at 9:48 AM, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo before launch there were these light artifacts in the videos.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EHide contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/mBj61HJ/KSP2-Anomaly-1.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022KSP2-Anomaly-1.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002298.42\u0022 height=\u0022659\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/mBj61HJ/KSP2-Anomaly-1.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/YbtM98V/KSP2-Anomaly-1-2.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022KSP2-Anomaly-1-2.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002271.00\u0022 height=\u0022753\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/YbtM98V/KSP2-Anomaly-1-2.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/Kzzs299/KSP2-Anomaly-2.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022KSP2-Anomaly-2.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002277.25\u0022 height=\u0022498\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/Kzzs299/KSP2-Anomaly-2.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/sQWyDMz/KSP2-Anomaly-3.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022KSP2-Anomaly-3.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022135.21\u0022 height=\u0022937\u0022 width=\u0022693\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/sQWyDMz/KSP2-Anomaly-3.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve gone flying in that direction and in other places and I can confirm that I have seen these lights also on the Runway Island and in the Desert. Also, sometimes when I fly over the place where the lights appeared / blinked, I sometimes hear a deep SWOOSH sound.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut, I have not yet found any anomalies that are linked to the lights. So I am not sure if they are a regular game video rendering bug or something more.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey\u0027re artifacts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve gone looking, too just to be sure... but the reality is they look exactly like rendering errors.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kroven","CreatedById":227196,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-03T23:24:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224251232\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022213185\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221677884861\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002255730\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jason_25\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, Jason_25 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am still willing to believe these could be actual UFOs.\u00A0 Something like the Brown Mountain Lights or Marpa lights or Naga Lights or probably several others.\u00A0 The lights are definitely multi colored and much larger than a single pixel.\u00A0 They zip by the first mountain in the north of the space center and the mountain that the island runway is on.\u00A0 They also move back and forth.\u00A0 But if there is something causing a crack in the terrain the very much more colorful skybox in this game could be leaking through.\u00A0 So it could go either way.\u00A0 I like to think someone is observing the progress at the space center as the Kerbals get closer and closer to being a spacefaring civilization.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWouldn\u0027t that be something lol.\u00A0 I would enjoy seeing how that would play out.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve seen strange color anomalies while zooming out from the flag at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E, like color or lighting has issues when scaling or something along those lines.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve chased those lights in the desert and mountains as well, but no results. They can outrun mach 4 lol.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rpatto92","CreatedById":145732,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-12T08:09:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWas up far too late flying a plane,\u00A0 when I seen these lights and thought that I seeing things. Perhaps just over tried.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGlad I\u0027m not the only one going nuts.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-12T08:20:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDevs should add them to the lore as Wilson Kerman marooned on an island signaling SOS with a mirror.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Cast\u002BAway\u002B-\u002BWilson.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002254.51\u0022 height=\u0022308\u0022 width=\u0022565\u0022 src=\u0022https://2.bp.blogspot.com/-50MNEv0USs0/UDCkrHex3BI/AAAAAAAAArQ/dmcxjDpO8oE/s1600/Cast\u002BAway\u002B-\u002BWilson.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/225122-dakota/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022225122\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/225122-dakota/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Dakota\u003C/a\u003Eg\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould you pass on the idea? Maybe someone likes it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}